This paper deals with the analysis and optimization of a wireless ad hoc network, specifically a barrage relay network. The paper discusses the behavior of individual controlled barrage regions (CBRs) and models them as a Markov process. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the network by finding the optimal size of each CBR, the number of relays contained within each CBR, the optimal relay locations, and the code rate that maximizes the transport capacity. This optimization aspect suggests that the paper could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the co-channel interference (CCI) between adjacent CBRs, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the transport capacity of the network, which suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
